# EKDP-032 / CDP-057 — `.eukoine/` single source

**Principle:** eulogikon `CDP-057` · EuKoine `EKDP-032` (`docs/governance/registry.yaml`).

**Canonical documents** (the only places that *state* this material):

| Document | States (canonically) |
|---|---|
| [`.eukoine/corpus_identity_and_schema.md`](.eukoine/corpus_identity_and_schema.md) | identity grid, v5, schema, `corpus_api` |
| [`.eukoine/interim_head_citation.md`](.eukoine/interim_head_citation.md) | interim head citation while passage identity is provisional |
| [`.eukoine/predicate_vocabulary.md`](.eukoine/predicate_vocabulary.md) | consult-before-coin obligation (shared code lexicon) |
| [`.eukoine/predicate_lexicon.yaml`](.eukoine/predicate_lexicon.yaml) | positive registry of baptised code signifiers |
| [`.eukoine/WRITE_ACCESS.md`](.eukoine/WRITE_ACCESS.md) | write protection, synchronizing-agent workflow, git safety |

## Agent obligations (every repo)

1. **Read freely** — use the canonical documents above.
2. **Pointer only elsewhere** — no summary, explanation, reinterpretation, or re-derivation of
   `.eukoine/` content in any other file (EKDP-004/005; rot G4). Cite by path; never copy
   normative prose.
3. **Never hand-edit a member's `.eukoine/` mirror** — there is one canonical copy at the hub; a
   member copy is a byte-identical output of `naming/sync.py`, so a hand-edit is drift, rejected by the
   content-bound guard. A change is made to the hub's canonical copy and re-synced — the cycle is
   drivable from any family repo ([`WRITE_ACCESS.md`](.eukoine/WRITE_ACCESS.md)).
4. **Drift** — fix the implementation; never patch the spec to match broken code.
5. **Code-lexicon compatibility** — every member's code and governing prose must
   stay compatible with
   [`.eukoine/predicate_lexicon.yaml`](.eukoine/predicate_lexicon.yaml). Consult
   [`.eukoine/predicate_vocabulary.md`](.eukoine/predicate_vocabulary.md) before
   coining. Do not introduce retired signifiers (`slug`, bare `unit`/`Unit`, bare
   `witness`, …). Existing debt is a finding to clear, not a licence to mint more.
